The course covers the development of European Union and its instiutions in legal and jurisdictional terms, the legal instruments of the EU, EU legislation and its relationship with national law, proceedings before the Court of Justice of the European Union, the principle of supremacy of the EU law and its relationship with national constitutions, and the protection of fundamental rights in the EU. The political implications of EU law and acquis will also be discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give an overview and understanding of the main principles of the EU law and of the legal system at the EU-level. The courses analyses the role of the courts and of the main jurisdictional bodies, the main sources (treaties and rulings), and the specific cases and disputes, also in relation to the national-supranational tension.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course, students will: 

- understand the European legal integration, the constitutive elements of the EU acquis; and legislative roles of the EU institutions; 

- analyse the main sources and principles of EU law, their implementation in the practice and their relation to other general principles of law; 

- understand and make distinction between different actions in the Court of Justice of the EU; choose the right remedy for a practical case; understand the procedural aspects and interpretation methods of the COJEU; 

- analyse a judgment of the COJEU and solve a case in the framework of the basic course according to the given questions/methodology.
